definitions.definition: Someone or something that farms , as:

subdefinitions.definition: A person who works the land and/or who keeps livestock ; anyone engaged in agriculture on a farm .
More specifically, a farm owner, as distinguished from a farmworker or farmhand as a hired employee thereof.

definitions.definition: One who takes taxes, customs, excise, or other duties, to collect for a certain rate per cent.
The lord of the field, or one who farms the lot and cope of the crown.
A regular person ; someone who did not receive a prestigious scholarship .
A baby farmer (operator of a rural orphanage).
